Gary Mabbutt was left with a 30inch scar on his left leg after his diabetes caused an artery to be clogged in 2013 . 
  The ex-Tottenham and England star was rushed to hospital for emergency surgery . 
  Surgeons replaced the main artery in his leg with a vein and needed 112 staples . 
  Doctors said it was 'touch and go' whether the leg would be amputated . 
  He was diagnosed with Type 1 diabetes at 17 . 
 